earch labs. For teams working on larger models, every cent counts and higher per-hour rates can lead to millions of dollars in higher training costs.‍Unveiling one of the largest ML compute clouds in the worldWith around 24,000 NVIDIA H100 GPUs, the Voltage Park cloud is one of the most powerful collections of cutting-edge ML compute in the world. Our clusters consist of 80GB H100 SXM5 GPUs fully interconnected with 3.2T InfiniBand. We currently offer bare-metal access for large-scale users that need peak performance. We will add support for short-term leases and hourly billing soon as we spin up our infrastructure along with support for familiar tools like Slurm, Kubernetes, and Mosaic for easy integration into existing training frameworks. Voltage Park clusters are already serving exciting AI companies, including Imbue, and are finalizing clusters for other AI leaders like Character.ai and Atomic AI. We expect our remaining compute to come online by early next year.“Voltage Park helped us access critical compute much more quickly than other providers could have,” said Kanjun Qiu, CEO of Imbue. “Our training requirements are demanding, and their team helped us get the very best performance out of our models (and with super responsive support, too). I hope their infrastructure helps more ML teams train and deploy state-of-the-art models fast.”As we build out our infrastructure, we want to hear from potential customers how we can engineer our clusters to support the use cases you need most, whether for experimentation, training, fine-tuning, or inference.Grab a spot on our waitlist by signing up on our website if you''re interested in compute, supply is first come first serve.If building a cloud infrastructure business from the ground up piques your interest, we’re hiring!Related articlesNo items found.Accessible AI Compute. Exceptional Customer Service.Deploy Now","metaDescription":"We''ve launched a massive next-generation cloud to support AI development and end the scramble for GPU access that''s dampering ML innovation","links":["https://www.voltagepark.com/blog/lightning-ai-voltage-park-merger-to-create-the-first-cloud-built-for-ai","https://imbue.com/?ref=blog.voltagepark.com","https://beta.character.ai/?ref=blog.voltagepark.com","https://atomic.ai/?ref=blog.voltagepark.com"],"scrapedAt":"2026-03-21T02:40:50.495Z"}],"scrapedAt":"2026-03-21T02:40:48.845Z"}','2026-03-21 02:40:50');
INSERT INTO research_notes VALUES('f74a2701-2506-46dd-add9-9e2b3203dad0','b58f75e0-5a7b-4775-8306-42b3c6702e27','https://voltagepark.com',unistr('Strong fit for GPU residual value coverage — $1B+ in H100 hardware, fully owned, no existing debt facility. Non-profit parent means treasury/risk conversation may go through Navigation Fund. Post-merger with Lightning AI, CFO/treasury contact may have changed. Jed McCaleb connection means unconventional decision chain. HIGH PRIORITY — large GPU fleet, no encumbrances.\u000a\u000aGPU scale: 24,000 NVIDIA H100 GPUs (~$1B worth), fully paid, zero debt, zero leasing. Expanded to 35,000+ H100/B200/GB300 post Lightning AI merger (Jan 2026). Six Tier 3 data centers in TX, VA, WA.\u000a\u000aFunding: Non-profit entity funded by billionaire Jed McCaleb (Mt. Gox / Ripple / Stellar wealth). Parent: Navigation Fund (non-profit). ~$500M initial H100 purchase in 2023.\u000a\u000aFinancing: No debt or leasing — fully equity-funded via Jed McCaleb / Navigation Fund. Merged with Lightning AI in January 2026.\u000a\u000aPartners: Lightning AI (merged Jan 2026); NVIDIA H100 partner\u000a\u000aRecent news:\u000a• January 2026: Merged with Lightning AI to create combined cloud with 35,000+ owned GPUs, growing from $18M to $500M ARR\u000a• 2025: Infrastructure grew to $1B in H100s across six Tier 3 data centers\u000a• Pricing as low as $1.89/hr per GPU — deliberately below-market due to non-profit mission'),'{"name":"Voltage Park","priority":"A","domain":"voltagepark.com","contacts":[{"name":"Eric Park","title":"CEO","email":"epark@voltagepark.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/voltage-park","source":"press coverage, Data Center Dynamics","confidence":"medium","email_confidence":"low — inferred from flast@ pattern (59.7% common)"}],"details":{"gpu_scale":"24,000 NVIDIA H100 GPUs (~$1B worth), fully paid, zero debt, zero leasing. Expanded to 35,000+ H100/B200/GB300 post Lightning AI merger (Jan 2026). Six Tier 3 data centers in TX, VA, WA.","recent_funding":"Non-profit entity funded by billionaire Jed McCaleb (Mt. Gox / Ripple / Stellar wealth). Parent: Navigation Fund (non-profit). ~$500M initial H100 purchase in 2023.","financing_activity":"No debt or leasing — fully equity-funded via Jed McCaleb / Navigation Fund. Merged with Lightning AI in January 2026.","key_partnerships":"Lightning AI (merged Jan 2026); NVIDIA H100 partner","email_pattern":"flast@voltagepark.com (59.7% usage) or firstname@voltagepark.com"},"recent_news":["January 2026: Merged with Lightning AI to create combined cloud with 35,000+ owned GPUs, growing from $18M to $500M ARR","2025: Infrastructure grew to $1B in H100s across six Tier 3 data centers","Pricing as low as $1.89/hr per GPU — deliberately below-market due to non-profit mission"],"qualification_notes":"Strong fit for GPU residual value coverage — $1B+ in H100 hardware, fully owned, no existing debt facility. Non-profit parent means treasury/risk conversation may go through Navigation Fund. Post-merger with Lightning AI, CFO/treasury contact may have changed. Jed McCaleb connection means unconventional decision chain. HIGH PRIORITY — large GPU fleet, no encumbrances."}','2026-03-21 02:49:33');
INSERT INTO research_notes VALUES('da0c8494-7a4c-44d7-ab54-1db8ca7adb33','07eac672-a04b-47e9-a734-5dda212bd3b2','https://vultr.com',unistr('Good fit — massive scale, recent equity + debt raises show sophisticated finance function. Already has banking relationships (JPM, BofA, GS). May be hard to break in given existing facility. Matt Short (SVP Finance) is the key contact for treasury/residual value discussion. CFO title not filled externally.\u000a\u000aGPU scale: Large GPU fleet (scale undisclosed publicly), enterprise GPU cloud platform. AI-focused cloud with $3.5B valuation.\u000a\u000aFunding: December 2024: $333M Series D at $3.5B valuation, co-led by AMD Ventures and LuminArx Capital Management. First outside funding after 10+ years bootstrapped.\u000a\u000aFinancing: June 2025: $329M syndicated credit facility led by J.P. Morgan, Bank of America, Wells Fargo; also Citi, Goldman Sachs, KeyBank.\u000a\u000aPartners: AMD Ventures (lead investor), LuminArx Capital, JP Morgan, BofA, Wells Fargo, Goldman Sachs\u000a\u000aRecent news:\u000a• Dec 2024: $333M at $3.5B valuation — first equity round ever, bootstrapped 10+ years\u000a• June 2025: $329M credit facility from major banks (JP Morgan, BofA, WF, Citi, GS, KeyBank)\u000a• 2024: Hired Amit Rai (GM of AI & Enterprise Cloud from ZoomInfo) and Nathan Goulding (SVP Engineering from Equinix)\u000a• World''s largest privately-held cloud computing company pre-Series D'),'{"name":"Vultr","priority":"A","domain":"vultr.com","contacts":[{"name":"J.J. Kardwell","title":"CEO","email":"jj.kardwell@vultr.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/vultr-holdings-llc","source":"Vultr website, Wikipedia, Business Wire","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"medium — first.last@ pattern common for tech companies"},{"name":"David Aninowsky","title":"Founder & Executive Chairman","email":"david.aninowsky@vultr.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/david-aninowsky-b1241924","source":"Wikipedia, Crunchbase","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"medium"},{"name":"Matt Short","title":"SVP Global Finance & Accounting (de facto CFO)","email":"matt.short@vultr.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/vultr-holdings-llc","source":"Vultr team page, Business Wire","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"medium"}],"details":{"gpu_scale":"Large GPU fleet (scale undisclosed publicly), enterprise GPU cloud platform. AI-focused cloud with $3.5B valuation.","recent_funding":"December 2024: $333M Series D at $3.5B valuation, co-led by AMD Ventures and LuminArx Capital Management. First outside funding after 10+ years bootstrapped.","financing_activity":"June 2025: $329M syndicated credit facility led by J.P. Morgan, Bank of America, Wells Fargo; also Citi, Goldman Sachs, KeyBank.","key_partnerships":"AMD Ventures (lead investor), LuminArx Capital, JP Morgan, BofA, Wells Fargo, Goldman Sachs","email_pattern":"first.last@vultr.com (likely, standard for tech cos of this size)"},"recent_news":["Dec 2024: $333M at $3.5B valuation — first equity round ever, bootstrapped 10+ years","June 2025: $329M credit facility from major banks (JP Morgan, BofA, WF, Citi, GS, KeyBank)","2024: Hired Amit Rai (GM of AI & Enterprise Cloud from ZoomInfo) and Nathan Goulding (SVP Engineering from Equinix)","World''s largest privately-held cloud computing company pre-Series D"],"qualification_notes":"Good fit — massive scale, recent equity + debt raises show sophisticated finance function. Already has banking relationships (JPM, BofA, GS). May be hard to break in given existing facility. Matt Short (SVP Finance) is the key contact for treasury/residual value discussion. CFO title not filled externally."}','2026-03-21 02:49:33');
INSERT INTO research_notes VALUES('692e50f9-11bc-48aa-a2f3-e4dfeb47b991','3cd5adb0-a4c0-4ea0-88cd-dc3fdc4f0ce6','https://genesiscloud.com',unistr('Moderate fit — smaller scale European GPU cloud, but CFO Christopher Heberlein is identified and reachable. No debt facility found = potential greenfield. German HQ may mean legal complexity.\u000a\u000aGPU scale: NVIDIA partner for Enterprise AI since 2018. $37M raised. Scale not publicly disclosed but smaller than US-based neoclouds.\u000a\u000aFunding: Total raised: ~$37M. Last disclosed round not specified — backed by Genesis Mining''s Marco Streng.\u000a\u000aFinancing: No recent debt facility found publicly.\u000a\u000aPartners: NVIDIA Partner Network, Richard Socher advisory board\u000a\u000aRecent news:\u000a• April 2025: Hired Oliver Dlugosch as Chief Growth Officer\u000a• Joined EU AI Champions Initiative\u000a• Ongoing: Building out European GPU cloud for Enterprise AI, GenAI, ML, rendering'),'{"name":"Genesis Cloud","priority":"A","domain":"genesiscloud.com","contacts":[{"name":"Dr. Stefan Schiefer","title":"CEO","email":"stefan.schiefer@genesiscloud.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/dr-stefan-schiefer/","source":"Genesis Cloud about page, RocketReach","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"medium — first.last@ common for German tech SMEs"},{"name":"Christopher Heberlein","title":"CFO","email":"christopher.heberlein@genesiscloud.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/genesiscloud","source":"The Org, RocketReach","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"medium"},{"name":"Oliver Dlugosch","title":"Chief Growth Officer","email":"oliver.dlugosch@genesiscloud.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/oliver-dlugosch","source":"TheOrg, X/Twitter announcement Apr 2025","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"medium"},{"name":"Nicolás Chaparro","title":"COO","email":"nicolas.chaparro@genesiscloud.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/genesiscloud","source":"Genesis Cloud leadership page","confidence":"medium","email_confidence":"medium"}],"details":{"gpu_scale":"NVIDIA partner for Enterprise AI since 2018. $37M raised. Scale not publicly disclosed but smaller than US-based neoclouds.","recent_funding":"Total raised: ~$37M. Last disclosed round not specified — backed by Genesis Mining''s Marco Streng.","financing_activity":"No recent debt facility found publicly.","key_partnerships":"NVIDIA Partner Network, Richard Socher advisory board","email_pattern":"first.last@genesiscloud.com (confirmed via multiple sources)"},"recent_news":["April 2025: Hired Oliver Dlugosch as Chief Growth Officer","Joined EU AI Champions Initiative","Ongoing: Building out European GPU cloud for Enterprise AI, GenAI, ML, rendering"],"qualification_notes":"Moderate fit — smaller scale European GPU cloud, but CFO Christopher Heberlein is identified and reachable. No debt facility found = potential greenfield. German HQ may mean legal complexity."}','2026-03-21 02:49:33');
INSERT INTO research_notes VALUES('82873310-fd70-4c7c-8e8c-7fbde0f04ebe','0a01cc52-7454-4a00-9e58-0649d150ef22','https://cirrascale.com',unistr('Good fit — unique multi-vendor GPU infrastructure, active deployment at scale. No identified CFO/finance lead — David Driggers is CEO/CTO combo, likely handles major financial decisions. Acquisition by BOXX means there''s a parent company finance structure to navigate. Residual value coverage conversation may need to go through BOXX.\u000a\u000aGPU scale: Multi-GPU dedicated cloud: NVIDIA (HGX H200, HGX B200/Blackwell), AMD, Cerebras, Qualcomm. AI Innovation Cloud. Only GPUaaS partnering with all major chip vendors.\u000a\u000aFunding: Acquired by BOXX in May 2017. Funding history unclear ($2M–$57M range cited across sources — likely confusion). No recent public raise.\u000a\u000aFinancing: No recent public debt or equity raise found. Ai2 partnership ($152M NSF/NVIDIA AI initiative).\u000a\u000aPartners: NVIDIA, AMD, Cerebras, Qualcomm, Ai2 (Allen Institute for AI), NSF\u000a\u000aRecent news:\u000a• 2026: Ai2 partners with Cirrascale to commercialize open-source AI models (NSF/NVIDIA $152M initiative)\u000a• 2025-2026: Added NVIDIA HGX B200 (Blackwell) to AI Innovation Cloud\u000a• 2026: Alex Nataros appointed CTO\u000a• Ongoing: Only GPUaaS provider with NVIDIA + AMD + Cerebras + Qualcomm partnerships'),'{"name":"Cirrascale Cloud Services","priority":"A","domain":"cirrascale.com","contacts":[{"name":"David Driggers","title":"CEO & CTO","email":"d.driggers@cirrascale.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/ddriggers/","source":"Cirrascale website, ZoomInfo (email format d***@cirrascale.com), DataCenterDynamics","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"medium — ZoomInfo shows d***@cirrascale.com, consistent with d.last@ pattern"},{"name":"PJ GO","title":"CEO (possible current or prior role — verify)","email":"pj.go@cirrascale.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/pj-go-644886142/","source":"LinkedIn profile","confidence":"low — may be historical or division-level CEO","email_confidence":"low"},{"name":"Alex Nataros","title":"CTO (appointed 2026)","email":"a.nataros@cirrascale.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/alex-nataros-ab07b2257/","source":"Intelligence360 news, 2026","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"low"}],"details":{"gpu_scale":"Multi-GPU dedicated cloud: NVIDIA (HGX H200, HGX B200/Blackwell), AMD, Cerebras, Qualcomm. AI Innovation Cloud. Only GPUaaS partnering with all major chip vendors.","recent_funding":"Acquired by BOXX in May 2017. Funding history unclear ($2M–$57M range cited across sources — likely confusion). No recent public raise.","financing_activity":"No recent public debt or equity raise found. Ai2 partnership ($152M NSF/NVIDIA AI initiative).","key_partnerships":"NVIDIA, AMD, Cerebras, Qualcomm, Ai2 (Allen Institute for AI), NSF","email_pattern":"first_initial.last@cirrascale.com (d***@cirrascale.com for Driggers confirmed via ZoomInfo)"},"recent_news":["2026: Ai2 partners with Cirrascale to commercialize open-source AI models (NSF/NVIDIA $152M initiative)","2025-2026: Added NVIDIA HGX B200 (Blackwell) to AI Innovation Cloud","2026: Alex Nataros appointed CTO","Ongoing: Only GPUaaS provider with NVIDIA + AMD + Cerebras + Qualcomm partnerships"],"qualification_notes":"Good fit — unique multi-vendor GPU infrastructure, active deployment at scale. No identified CFO/finance lead — David Driggers is CEO/CTO combo, likely handles major financial decisions. Acquisition by BOXX means there''s a parent company finance structure to navigate. Residual value coverage conversation may need to go through BOXX."}','2026-03-21 02:49:33');
INSERT INTO research_notes VALUES('daf7e959-4e3c-48bc-bbf8-8c8199a90e9f','22530fe7-5fc8-4a56-8df0-8b57774cfda5','https://tensorwave.com',unistr('Strong fit — AMD-focused neocloud with large GPU fleet and fresh capital. No debt identified beyond equity rounds. Magnetar Capital involvement is interesting — they''re a sophisticated credit investor. 40-person team scaling to 100+ means finance function is still lean. COO Piotr Tomasik likely handles operational finance. No dedicated CFO identified — worth checking.\u000a\u000aGPU scale: 8,000 AMD Instinct MI325X GPUs in dedicated training cluster. Liquid-cooled. Building world''s largest liquid-cooled AMD GPU deployment. Run-rate revenue target: $100M+ by end of 2025 (20x YoY).\u000a\u000aFunding: October 2024: $43M SAFE led by Nexus VP. May 2025: $100M Series A led by Magnetar and AMD Ventures. Total raised: $146.7M.\u000a\u000aFinancing: $100M Series A (May 2025) — used for AMD GPU cluster expansion. Magnetar, AMD Ventures, Maverick Silicon, Nexus VP, Prosperity7.\u000a\u000aPartners: AMD (preferred cloud partner), Magnetar Capital, Nexus Venture Partners, AMD Ventures\u000a\u000aRecent news:\u000a• May 2025: $100M Series A co-led by Magnetar and AMD Ventures to build 8,000+ AMD GPU cluster\u000a• October 2024: $43M SAFE (largest in Nevada startup history)\u000a• 2025: Deployed 8,000 AMD MI325X GPUs as dedicated training cluster\u000a• On track for $100M+ ARR in 2025 (20x growth from prior year)'),'{"name":"TensorWave","priority":"A","domain":"tensorwave.com","contacts":[{"name":"Darrick Horton","title":"CEO & Co-Founder","email":"darrick.horton@tensorwave.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/tensorwave","source":"TechCrunch, Business Wire, SiliconAngle","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"low — pattern guessed"},{"name":"Piotr Tomasik","title":"COO & President","email":"piotr.tomasik@tensorwave.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/tensorwave","source":"Business Wire Series A announcement","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"low"},{"name":"Jeff Tatarchuk","title":"Co-Founder & Chief Growth Officer","email":"jeff.tatarchuk@tensorwave.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/tensorwave","source":"SiliconAngle, Business Wire","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"low"}],"details":{"gpu_scale":"8,000 AMD Instinct MI325X GPUs in dedicated training cluster. Liquid-cooled. Building world''s largest liquid-cooled AMD GPU deployment. Run-rate revenue target: $100M+ by end of 2025 (20x YoY).","recent_funding":"October 2024: $43M SAFE led by Nexus VP. May 2025: $100M Series A led by Magnetar and AMD Ventures. Total raised: $146.7M.","financing_activity":"$100M Series A (May 2025) — used for AMD GPU cluster expansion. Magnetar, AMD Ventures, Maverick Silicon, Nexus VP, Prosperity7.","key_partnerships":"AMD (preferred cloud partner), Magnetar Capital, Nexus Venture Partners, AMD Ventures","email_pattern":"Unknown — company is ~3 years old, likely first.last@tensorwave.com"},"recent_news":["May 2025: $100M Series A co-led by Magnetar and AMD Ventures to build 8,000+ AMD GPU cluster","October 2024: $43M SAFE (largest in Nevada startup history)","2025: Deployed 8,000 AMD MI325X GPUs as dedicated training cluster","On track for $100M+ ARR in 2025 (20x growth from prior year)"],"qualification_notes":"Strong fit — AMD-focused neocloud with large GPU fleet and fresh capital. No debt identified beyond equity rounds. Magnetar Capital involvement is interesting — they''re a sophisticated credit investor. 40-person team scaling to 100+ means finance function is still lean. COO Piotr Tomasik likely handles operational finance. No dedicated CFO identified — worth checking."}','2026-03-21 02:49:33');
INSERT INTO research_notes VALUES('066a2451-29e6-47fa-ba05-bd050726f546','eeab4f25-1dbf-465c-a512-5c9618546fda','https://hyperbolic.xyz',unistr('Weak-to-moderate fit — Hyperbolic is a marketplace/aggregator, not an owned-GPU operator. They don''t hold hardware assets so residual value coverage is less directly applicable. However, if they''re facilitating large GPU transactions, there may be a play. Small $20M total raise — early stage. CEO Jasper Zhang is primary contact.\u000a\u000aGPU scale: Decentralized GPU marketplace — aggregates idle GPU capacity globally. No owned hardware fleet. Serverless inference platform.\u000a\u000aFunding: July 2024: $7M seed led by Polychain Capital + Lightspeed Faction. December 2024: $12M Series A led by Variant Fund + Polychain. Total: $20M.\u000a\u000aFinancing: Equity only. No debt facility identified.\u000a\u000aPartners: Polychain Capital, Variant Fund, Lightspeed Faction, EigenLayer (Sreeram Kannan angel)\u000a\u000aRecent news:\u000a• December 2024: $12M Series A — total $20M raised\u000a• Launched cloud-hosted GPU marketplace aggregating global idle GPUs\u000a• Blockchain-based verifiable inference technology\u000a• UC Berkeley and UW founders — math Ph.D. background'),'{"name":"Hyperbolic","priority":"A","domain":"hyperbolic.xyz","contacts":[{"name":"Jasper Zhang (Jasper Yue Zhang)","title":"CEO & Co-Founder","email":"jasper@hyperbolic.xyz","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/hyperboliclabs","source":"Hyperbolic blog, SiliconAngle, Fortune","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"medium — crypto/web3-adjacent startups often use first@domain"},{"name":"Yuchen Jin","title":"Co-Founder","email":"yuchen@hyperbolic.xyz","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/hyperboliclabs","source":"Hyperbolic blog, SiliconAngle","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"medium"}],"details":{"gpu_scale":"Decentralized GPU marketplace — aggregates idle GPU capacity globally. No owned hardware fleet. Serverless inference platform.","recent_funding":"July 2024: $7M seed led by Polychain Capital + Lightspeed Faction. December 2024: $12M Series A led by Variant Fund + Polychain. Total: $20M.","financing_activity":"Equity only. No debt facility identified.","key_partnerships":"Polychain Capital, Variant Fund, Lightspeed Faction, EigenLayer (Sreeram Kannan angel)","email_pattern":"first@hyperbolic.xyz likely (web3/crypto startup pattern)"},"recent_news":["December 2024: $12M Series A — total $20M raised","Launched cloud-hosted GPU marketplace aggregating global idle GPUs","Blockchain-based verifiable inference technology","UC Berkeley and UW founders — math Ph.D. background"],"qualification_notes":"Weak-to-moderate fit — Hyperbolic is a marketplace/aggregator, not an owned-GPU operator. They don''t hold hardware assets so residual value coverage is less directly applicable. However, if they''re facilitating large GPU transactions, there may be a play. Small $20M total raise — early stage. CEO Jasper Zhang is primary contact."}','2026-03-21 02:49:33');
INSERT INTO research_notes VALUES('a9b1db46-10a6-4ec8-9bcf-3a6a91d803ca','c31ae2a5-6a69-437c-a157-4c99dfc66752','https://cudocompute.com',unistr('Moderate fit — NVIDIA Cloud Partner with real GPU infrastructure but funding scale unclear. UK-based HQ adds complexity. Matt Hawkins is both CEO of Ventures and CEO of Compute — single point of contact.\u000a\u000aGPU scale: NVIDIA Cloud Partner (NCP). Designs, commissions, and operates NVIDIA GPU clusters. ISO 27001-certified facilities in UK, EU, North America, APAC, Middle East.\u000a\u000aFunding: Earlier: £7M of £10M target (CUDOS blockchain token raise). Recent external raise undisclosed (GD10 Ventures invested).\u000a\u000aFinancing: GD10 Ventures investment (amount undisclosed). No recent large facility identified.\u000a\u000aPartners: NVIDIA Cloud Partner, GD10 Ventures. Parent: CUDO Ventures (800,000 users, 145 countries).\u000a\u000aRecent news:\u000a• 2025: Expanded NVIDIA GPU cluster operations across multiple regions\u000a• Ongoing: Land + Power + Compute as-a-service model for enterprise AI'),'{"name":"CUDO Compute","priority":"B","domain":"cudocompute.com","contacts":[{"name":"Matt Hawkins","title":"CEO & Founder","email":"matt.hawkins@cudocompute.com","linkedin":"https://uk.linkedin.com/in/mathewhawkins","source":"CUDO Ventures website, Crunchbase, TheOrg","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"low — pattern guessed"}],"details":{"gpu_scale":"NVIDIA Cloud Partner (NCP). Designs, commissions, and operates NVIDIA GPU clusters. ISO 27001-certified facilities in UK, EU, North America, APAC, Middle East.","recent_funding":"Earlier: £7M of £10M target (CUDOS blockchain token raise). Recent external raise undisclosed (GD10 Ventures invested).","financing_activity":"GD10 Ventures investment (amount undisclosed). No recent large facility identified.","key_partnerships":"NVIDIA Cloud Partner, GD10 Ventures. Parent: CUDO Ventures (800,000 users, 145 countries).","email_pattern":"first.last@cudocompute.com or first.last@cudoventures.com — unconfirmed"},"recent_news":["2025: Expanded NVIDIA GPU cluster operations across multiple regions","Ongoing: Land + Power + Compute as-a-service model for enterprise AI"],"qualification_notes":"Moderate fit — NVIDIA Cloud Partner with real GPU infrastructure but funding scale unclear. UK-based HQ adds complexity. Matt Hawkins is both CEO of Ventures and CEO of Compute — single point of contact."}','2026-03-21 02:49:33');
INSERT INTO research_notes VALUES('fa216433-3062-4499-8293-5baff5a7777d','d1936709-8e87-4b91-9e13-a8d44c1abd6c','https://ori.co',unistr('Complex — recently acquired by Brookfield''s Radiant (Feb 2026). Decision-making now goes through Radiant/Brookfield. Mahdi Yahya is now president of Radiant. This may actually be a bigger opportunity given Brookfield''s balance sheet and appetite for structured finance.\u000a\u000aGPU scale: 1,024 NVIDIA H100s in private cloud cluster (announced). UK-based pay-as-you-go AI compute provider across Europe.\u000a\u000aFunding: 2025: $140M raise. Total raised: $178M across 3 rounds. Saudi Aramco VC invested.\u000a\u000aFinancing: February 2026: Acquired by Brookfield''s Radiant. Terms undisclosed.\u000a\u000aPartners: Saudi Aramco Energy Ventures, Brookfield Asset Management (via Radiant acquisition Feb 2026)\u000a\u000aRecent news:\u000a• February 2026: Acquired by Brookfield''s Radiant — combined AI cloud platform\u000a• 2025: Raised $140M, total $178M raised\u000a• Deployed 1,024 H100 private cloud cluster\u000a• Undisclosed Saudi Aramco VC investment'),'{"name":"Ori Industries","priority":"B","domain":"ori.co","contacts":[{"name":"Mahdi Yahya","title":"CEO & Co-Founder (now President, Radiant)","email":"mahdi@ori.co","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/ori-industries","source":"Sifted, Crunchbase, BeBeez","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"low — acquired by Radiant/Brookfield Feb 2026"}],"details":{"gpu_scale":"1,024 NVIDIA H100s in private cloud cluster (announced). UK-based pay-as-you-go AI compute provider across Europe.","recent_funding":"2025: $140M raise. Total raised: $178M across 3 rounds. Saudi Aramco VC invested.","financing_activity":"February 2026: Acquired by Brookfield''s Radiant. Terms undisclosed.","key_partnerships":"Saudi Aramco Energy Ventures, Brookfield Asset Management (via Radiant acquisition Feb 2026)","email_pattern":"first@ori.co likely (small startup pattern)"},"recent_news":["February 2026: Acquired by Brookfield''s Radiant — combined AI cloud platform","2025: Raised $140M, total $178M raised","Deployed 1,024 H100 private cloud cluster","Undisclosed Saudi Aramco VC investment"],"qualification_notes":"Complex — recently acquired by Brookfield''s Radiant (Feb 2026). Decision-making now goes through Radiant/Brookfield. Mahdi Yahya is now president of Radiant. This may actually be a bigger opportunity given Brookfield''s balance sheet and appetite for structured finance."}','2026-03-21 02:49:33');
INSERT INTO research_notes VALUES('831c89dc-faa5-45f4-94c9-0fcf3e4c029b','1267a741-f052-45a2-96f6-1e6222e1c8ba','https://phoenixnap.com',unistr('Uncertain — in the middle of M&A/restructuring activity. Goldman sale process and asset divestiture make this a complicated target right now. GPU scale is real but management attention is on M&A. Could be a good post-acquisition conversation if buyer is identified.\u000a\u000aGPU scale: Bare metal cloud with GPU servers (NVIDIA Tesla and newer). Hybrid cloud/dedicated server provider. Medium-scale GPU infrastructure.\u000a\u000aFunding: Jan 2025: Goldman Sachs running sale process for phoenixNAP. Q2 2026: Sold Phoenix colocation facility to RadiusDC. Focus shifting to core cloud/infrastructure services.\u000a\u000aFinancing: Goldman Sachs-led sale process (Jan 2025). Divesting physical data center assets.\u000a\u000aPartners: NVIDIA (GPU servers), Goldman Sachs (M&A advisor)\u000a\u000aRecent news:\u000a• Q2 2026: Sold Phoenix colocation facility to RadiusDC\u000a• January 2025: Goldman Sachs running sale process for phoenixNAP\u000a• Restructuring: divesting data center assets, focusing on core cloud services'),'{"name":"phoenixNAP","priority":"B","domain":"phoenixnap.com","contacts":[{"name":"Ron Cadwell","title":"CEO","email":"ron.cadwell@phoenixnap.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/ron-cadwell-0b747313b/","source":"Comparably, Tracxn","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"low — pattern guessed"},{"name":"Ian McClarty","title":"Founder & President","email":"ian.mcclarty@phoenixnap.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/mcclarty","source":"Comparably, press releases","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"low"},{"name":"William Bell","title":"EVP of Products","email":"william.bell@phoenixnap.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/phoenixnap","source":"Comparably leadership page","confidence":"medium","email_confidence":"low"}],"details":{"gpu_scale":"Bare metal cloud with GPU servers (NVIDIA Tesla and newer). Hybrid cloud/dedicated server provider. Medium-scale GPU infrastructure.","recent_funding":"Jan 2025: Goldman Sachs running sale process for phoenixNAP. Q2 2026: Sold Phoenix colocation facility to RadiusDC. Focus shifting to core cloud/infrastructure services.","financing_activity":"Goldman Sachs-led sale process (Jan 2025). Divesting physical data center assets.","key_partnerships":"NVIDIA (GPU servers), Goldman Sachs (M&A advisor)","email_pattern":"first.last@phoenixnap.com (likely)"},"recent_news":["Q2 2026: Sold Phoenix colocation facility to RadiusDC","January 2025: Goldman Sachs running sale process for phoenixNAP","Restructuring: divesting data center assets, focusing on core cloud services"],"qualification_notes":"Uncertain — in the middle of M&A/restructuring activity. Goldman sale process and asset divestiture make this a complicated target right now. GPU scale is real but management attention is on M&A. Could be a good post-acquisition conversation if buyer is identified."}','2026-03-21 02:49:33');
INSERT INTO research_notes VALUES('196d02d9-b9b1-4faa-bed8-18c8d0118afa','43cb889d-113f-4076-bfca-cd71f73bec9e','https://colovore.com',unistr('Very relevant — GPU-dense colocation with $925M Blackstone facility. Already has sophisticated financing in place. CFO Ben Coughlin is identified. King Street Capital is the owner (see Priority C). The residual value conversation fits perfectly with their expansion plan. May be fully covered by Blackstone facility.\u000a\u000aGPU scale: Ultra-high-density liquid-cooled colocation for AI/GPU. Up to 250kW/cabinet (500kW+ with direct liquid cooling). NVIDIA DGX Ready certified. Thousands of DGX/GPU servers in operation. Sites: Santa Clara (2x9MW), Reno, Chicago, Austin (planned).\u000a\u000aFunding: May 2024: Acquired by King Street Capital. May 2025: $925M debt facility from Blackstone.\u000a\u000aFinancing: $925M Blackstone debt facility (May 2025) for national AI data center expansion. King Street Capital is the equity sponsor.\u000a\u000aPartners: King Street Capital (owner), Blackstone (debt facility), NVIDIA (DGX Ready partner)\u000a\u000aRecent news:\u000a• May 2025: $925M Blackstone debt facility for AI data center expansion\u000a• May 2025: Jeffrey Springborn appointed CEO\u000a• November 2024: Opened second 9MW liquid-cooled data center in Santa Clara\u000a• May 2024: Acquired by King Street Capital'),'{"name":"Colovore","priority":"B","domain":"colovore.com","contacts":[{"name":"Jeffrey Springborn","title":"CEO (appointed May 2025)","email":"jeff.springborn@colovore.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/colovore","source":"Business Wire, DCD, May 2025","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"low"},{"name":"Ben Coughlin","title":"Co-Founder & CFO","email":"ben.coughlin@colovore.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/colovore","source":"Colovore about page","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"low"},{"name":"Sean Holzknecht","title":"President & Co-Founder","email":"sean.holzknecht@colovore.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/colovore","source":"Colovore about page","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"low"},{"name":"Peter Harrison","title":"CTO & Co-Founder","email":"peter.harrison@colovore.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/colovore","source":"Colovore about page","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"low"}],"details":{"gpu_scale":"Ultra-high-density liquid-cooled colocation for AI/GPU. Up to 250kW/cabinet (500kW+ with direct liquid cooling). NVIDIA DGX Ready certified. Thousands of DGX/GPU servers in operation. Sites: Santa Clara (2x9MW), Reno, Chicago, Austin (planned).","recent_funding":"May 2024: Acquired by King Street Capital. May 2025: $925M debt facility from Blackstone.","financing_activity":"$925M Blackstone debt facility (May 2025) for national AI data center expansion. King Street Capital is the equity sponsor.","key_partnerships":"King Street Capital (owner), Blackstone (debt facility), NVIDIA (DGX Ready partner)","email_pattern":"first.last@colovore.com (likely — startup culture)"},"recent_news":["May 2025: $925M Blackstone debt facility for AI data center expansion","May 2025: Jeffrey Springborn appointed CEO","November 2024: Opened second 9MW liquid-cooled data center in Santa Clara","May 2024: Acquired by King Street Capital"],"qualification_notes":"Very relevant — GPU-dense colocation with $925M Blackstone facility. Already has sophisticated financing in place. CFO Ben Coughlin is identified. King Street Capital is the owner (see Priority C). The residual value conversation fits perfectly with their expansion plan. May be fully covered by Blackstone facility."}','2026-03-21 02:49:33');
INSERT INTO research_notes VALUES('2be81b4c-c2f3-41a4-8634-cc4d606ed67b','4466d29b-d07a-4620-9862-74dc5923fe37','https://upper90.io',unistr('This is a PARTNER not a target customer. Upper90 is already doing GPU-collateralized lending — they''re a potential co-investor or referral partner for Corgi. They''ve already solved the GPU residual value problem themselves for at least one deal. Consider whether to approach as partner rather than outreach target.\u000a\u000aGPU scale: Not a GPU operator — they are a GPU-collateralized lender. $485M AUM. $1.5B+ total originations since 2018.\u000a\u000aFunding: N/A — investment firm\u000a\u000aFinancing: March 2025: Led $225M credit facility to Crusoe for NVIDIA GPU purchase (syndicated with BCI, FS Investments, King Street, Liberty Mutual Investments, ORIX USA). 2023: First GPU debt facility to Crusoe.\u000a\u000aPartners: Crusoe (key borrower), BCI, FS Investments, King Street Capital, Liberty Mutual Investments, ORIX USA (all syndication partners on Crusoe deal)\u000a\u000aRecent news:\u000a• March 2025: Closed $225M GPU credit facility for Crusoe, syndicated with BCI/FS/King Street/LMI/ORIX\u000a• 2023: Pioneered GPU debt facility for Crusoe (first in market)\u000a• $485M AUM, $1.5B+ total originations'),'{"name":"Upper90","priority":"B","domain":"upper90.io","contacts":[{"name":"Billy Libby","title":"CEO & Co-Founder","email":"billy@upper90.io","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/billy-libby-76464b1/","source":"ZoomInfo (b***@upper90.io confirmed), RocketReach, Multiple sources","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"high — ZoomInfo confirms b***@upper90.io = billy@upper90.io"},{"name":"Jason Finger","title":"Co-Founder & Chairman","email":"jason@upper90.io","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/upper90","source":"Upper90 team page","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"medium"},{"name":"William Geist","title":"Managing Partner","email":"william@upper90.io","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/upper90","source":"Upper90 team page","confidence":"medium","email_confidence":"low"}],"details":{"gpu_scale":"Not a GPU operator — they are a GPU-collateralized lender. $485M AUM. $1.5B+ total originations since 2018.","recent_funding":"N/A — investment firm","financing_activity":"March 2025: Led $225M credit facility to Crusoe for NVIDIA GPU purchase (syndicated with BCI, FS Investments, King Street, Liberty Mutual Investments, ORIX USA). 2023: First GPU debt facility to Crusoe.","key_partnerships":"Crusoe (key borrower), BCI, FS Investments, King Street Capital, Liberty Mutual Investments, ORIX USA (all syndication partners on Crusoe deal)","email_pattern":"firstname@upper90.io confirmed (billy@upper90.io verified)"},"recent_news":["March 2025: Closed $225M GPU credit facility for Crusoe, syndicated with BCI/FS/King Street/LMI/ORIX","2023: Pioneered GPU debt facility for Crusoe (first in market)","$485M AUM, $1.5B+ total originations"],"qualification_notes":"This is a PARTNER not a target customer. Upper90 is already doing GPU-collateralized lending — they''re a potential co-investor or referral partner for Corgi. They''ve already solved the GPU residual value problem themselves for at least one deal. Consider whether to approach as partner rather than outreach target."}','2026-03-21 02:49:33');
INSERT INTO research_notes VALUES('1dd59168-9baf-4dd3-bdfd-126c78aa50ce','5ffd4d22-d4a4-4c0f-9f65-e53947503483','https://victoryparkcapital.com',unistr('PARTNER potential — VPC is already doing GPU-backed credit. They''re a sophisticated lender not a hardware buyer. Like Upper90, consider partner/referral approach. Their Crusoe deals show they understand GPU residual value dynamics. Janus Henderson ownership gives them institutional capital backing.\u000a\u000aGPU scale: N/A — alternative asset manager / private credit firm. $28B+ AUM.\u000a\u000aFunding: August 2024: Majority acquired by Janus Henderson Group.\u000a\u000aFinancing: August 2025: $175M credit facility to Crusoe for Iceland data center (NVIDIA DGX + Blackwell GPUs). Active GPU-collateralized lender.\u000a\u000aPartners: Janus Henderson (majority owner), Crusoe (borrower), Latham & Watkins (legal)\u000a\u000aRecent news:\u000a• August 2025: $175M credit facility to Crusoe for Iceland GPU expansion with atNorth\u000a• August 2024: Majority-acquired by Janus Henderson Group\u000a• February 2024: Promoted Kinan Hayani and Sora Monachino to Managing Director'),'{"name":"Victory Park Capital","priority":"B","domain":"victoryparkcapital.com","contacts":[{"name":"Richard Levy","title":"CEO, CIO & Founder","email":"rlevy@victoryparkcapital.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/victory-park-capital-advisors","source":"Victory Park website, Janus Henderson acquisition doc","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"low — pattern guessed, firm uses ir@victoryparkcapital.com for general contact"},{"name":"Brendan Carroll","title":"Co-Founder & Senior Partner","email":"bcarroll@victoryparkcapital.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/victory-park-capital-advisors","source":"Victory Park website, Crain''s Chicago","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"low"},{"name":"Jeff Schneider","title":"COO & Partner","email":"jschneider@victoryparkcapital.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/victory-park-capital-advisors","source":"Victory Park team page","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"low"}],"details":{"gpu_scale":"N/A — alternative asset manager / private credit firm. $28B+ AUM.","recent_funding":"August 2024: Majority acquired by Janus Henderson Group.","financing_activity":"August 2025: $175M credit facility to Crusoe for Iceland data center (NVIDIA DGX + Blackwell GPUs). Active GPU-collateralized lender.","key_partnerships":"Janus Henderson (majority owner), Crusoe (borrower), Latham & Watkins (legal)","email_pattern":"initial+last@victoryparkcapital.com likely (e.g. rlevy@), general: ir@victoryparkcapital.com"},"recent_news":["August 2025: $175M credit facility to Crusoe for Iceland GPU expansion with atNorth","August 2024: Majority-acquired by Janus Henderson Group","February 2024: Promoted Kinan Hayani and Sora Monachino to Managing Director"],"qualification_notes":"PARTNER potential — VPC is already doing GPU-backed credit. They''re a sophisticated lender not a hardware buyer. Like Upper90, consider partner/referral approach. Their Crusoe deals show they understand GPU residual value dynamics. Janus Henderson ownership gives them institutional capital backing."}','2026-03-21 02:49:33');
INSERT INTO research_notes VALUES('56439caf-ee74-466d-bb35-03a5980e7d85','935a16bb-f197-420c-b48f-3cfa88fc02ad','https://orix.com',unistr('LENDER/PARTNER — ORIX USA is already active in GPU-backed credit (Crusoe deal). They''re a potential co-lender or distribution partner. Has deep infrastructure and technology lending expertise. Yvonne Zhu (CFO) and the Growth Capital team are the relevant contacts.\u000a\u000aGPU scale: N/A — large asset manager/lender. $52.9B in servicing/admin assets, $44B in funded assets.\u000a\u000aFunding: N/A — established firm (subsidiary of ORIX Corporation Japan).\u000a\u000aFinancing: March 2025: Participated in $225M GPU credit facility for Crusoe (led by Upper90, with BCI, FS Investments, King Street, Liberty Mutual). General contact: information@orix.com.\u000a\u000aPartners: Upper90 (Crusoe deal co-lender), Crusoe (borrower), ORIX Japan (parent)\u000a\u000aRecent news:\u000a• March 2025: Participated in $225M Crusoe GPU credit facility syndicate\u000a• May 2024: Yvonne Zhu named CFO\u000a• 2025: ORIX Rentec (Japan) launches GPU cloud service via Cloud4C partnership\u000a• ORIX USA $52.9B in AUM/managed assets as of Dec 2025'),'{"name":"ORIX USA","priority":"B","domain":"orix.com","contacts":[{"name":"Terry Suzuki","title":"President & CEO","email":"tsuzuki@orix.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/orix-usa","source":"ORIX USA website, OCP press release","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"low — large corporation, may use different pattern"},{"name":"Yvonne Zhu","title":"CFO (appointed May 2024)","email":"yzhu@orix.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/orix-usa","source":"ORIX USA news page (May 2024)","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"low"},{"name":"David Nishida","title":"COO & Group CFO","email":"dnishida@orix.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/orix-usa","source":"ORIX USA people page","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"low"}],"details":{"gpu_scale":"N/A — large asset manager/lender. $52.9B in servicing/admin assets, $44B in funded assets.","recent_funding":"N/A — established firm (subsidiary of ORIX Corporation Japan).","financing_activity":"March 2025: Participated in $225M GPU credit facility for Crusoe (led by Upper90, with BCI, FS Investments, King Street, Liberty Mutual). General contact: information@orix.com.","key_partnerships":"Upper90 (Crusoe deal co-lender), Crusoe (borrower), ORIX Japan (parent)","email_pattern":"initial+last@orix.com (e.g. tsuzuki@orix.com) — typical for large institutions, unconfirmed"},"recent_news":["March 2025: Participated in $225M Crusoe GPU credit facility syndicate","May 2024: Yvonne Zhu named CFO","2025: ORIX Rentec (Japan) launches GPU cloud service via Cloud4C partnership","ORIX USA $52.9B in AUM/managed assets as of Dec 2025"],"qualification_notes":"LENDER/PARTNER — ORIX USA is already active in GPU-backed credit (Crusoe deal). They''re a potential co-lender or distribution partner. Has deep infrastructure and technology lending expertise. Yvonne Zhu (CFO) and the Growth Capital team are the relevant contacts."}','2026-03-21 02:49:33');
INSERT INTO research_notes VALUES('38087df7-ae26-4c95-a62f-9b6edf3f1222','86f60581-89d9-499e-8f40-de5c80af164b','https://kingstreet.com',unistr('INVESTOR/PARTNER — King Street already owns Colovore (a GPU colocation operator). Brian Higgins personally endorsed Colovore CEO appointment. The Crusoe GPU credit facility also listed King Street as syndication partner. Very relevant to Corgi''s proposition — they clearly understand GPU collateral value. Approach as sophisticated co-investor.\u000a\u000aGPU scale: N/A — $30B global investment firm. Not a GPU operator.\u000a\u000aFunding: N/A — established fund.\u000a\u000aFinancing: May 2024: Acquired Colovore (GPU colocation operator). May 2025: Colovore closed $925M Blackstone debt facility under King Street ownership.\u000a\u000aPartners: Colovore (portfolio company), Blackstone (Colovore debt), 10 offices globally\u000a\u000aRecent news:\u000a• Dec 2025: Kris Mastronardi promoted to Partner (COO/Head of Strategy)\u000a• May 2025: Colovore (King Street portfolio) closes $925M Blackstone facility\u000a• May 2024: Acquired Colovore — King Street''s first data center investment'),'{"name":"King Street Capital Management","priority":"C","domain":"kingstreet.com","contacts":[{"name":"Brian Higgins","title":"Founder & Managing Partner","email":"bhiggins@kingstreet.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/brian-higgins-kingstreet/","source":"King Street website, Bloomberg","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"low — pattern guessed, not publicly disclosed"},{"name":"Kris Mastronardi","title":"COO & Global Head of Strategy (promoted to Partner Dec 2025)","email":"kmastronardi@kingstreet.com","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/company/kingstreet-capital-management","source":"PR Newswire, Dec 2025","confidence":"high","email_confidence":"low"}],"details":{"gpu_scale":"N/A — $30B global investment firm. Not a GPU operator.","recent_funding":"N/A — established fund.","financing_activity":"May 2024: Acquired Colovore (GPU colocation operator). May 2025: Colovore closed $925M Blackstone debt facility under King Street ownership.","key_partnerships":"Colovore (portfolio company), Blackstone (Colovore debt), 10 offices globally","email_pattern":"initial+last@kingstreet.com (guessed). HQ: 299 Park Ave 40F, NYC 10171. Phone: (212) 812-3100"},"recent_news":["Dec 2025: Kris Mastronardi promoted to Partner (COO/Head of Strategy)","May 2025: Colovore (King Street portfolio) closes $925M Blackstone facility","May 2024: Acquired Colovore — King Street''s first data center investment"],"qualification_notes":"INVESTOR/PARTNER — King Street already owns Colovore (a GPU colocation operator). Brian Higgins personally endorsed Colovore CEO appointment. The Crusoe GPU credit facility also listed King Street as syndication partner. Very relevant to Corgi''s proposition — they clearly understand GPU collateral value. Approach as sophisticated co-investor."}','2026-03-21 02:49:33');
